@graph.description: BusyBox combines tiny versions of many common UNIX utilities into a single small executable. @graph.description: This package contains helper tools that are necessary for switching between the various init systems that Debian contains (e. g. sysvinit or systemd). An example is deb-systemd-helper, a script that enables systemd unit files without depending on a running systemd. It also includes the \"service\", \"invoke-rc.d\", and \"update-rc.d\" scripts which provide an abstraction for enabling, disabling, starting, and stopping services for all supported Debian init systems as specified by the policy. While this package is maintained by pkg-systemd-maintainers, it is NOT specific to systemd at all. Maintainers of other init systems are welcome to include their helpers in this package.
@graph.name: init-system-helpers-service
@graph.summary: helper tools for all init systems
